{
  "modId": 13466.0,
  "modName": "RIS - Real Ice and Snow",
  "summary": "Snow that looks like real snow. Icicles that look like real icicles. Icebergs that look like real icebergs. Icefloes that look like real icefloes.",
  "descriptionHtml": "[img]http://i.imgur.com/UJ12AJk.png[/img]\r<br />[center]\r<br />      The Elder Scrolls V\r<br />                  SKYRIM: \r<br />                     \r<br />         [size=4]Real Ice & Snow[/size]\r<br />               by grVulture\r<br />           \r<br />      [/center]\r<br />[img]http://i.imgur.com/UJ12AJk.png[/img]\r<br />\r<br />UPDATE: Realistic Icicle:\r<br />Big Icicles are watery but not transparent (they are old ice accumulating to an icicle), small icicles are transparent (they \r<br />are fresh).\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />[youtube]fGlzVrerTho[/youtube]\r<br />\r<br />[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/65163/?][img]http://staticdelivery.nexusmods.com/mods/110/images/65163-1-1430071785.png[/img][/url]\r<br />\r<br />[youtube]mtfDNZbNW6Y[/youtube]\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />\r<br />     1. INSTALLING THE PLUGIN\r<br />\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />\r<br />BE SURE TO BACKUP YOUR ORIGINAL TEXTURES, in case you decide that\r<br />these textures are not for you.\r<br />\r<br />To install, unzip the RIS.7z\r<br />file into your Skyrim directory. Be sure to allow overwriting old\r<br />files.\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />\r<br />     2. PLAYING THE PLUGIN\r<br />\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />\r<br />This is a collection of textures that replace the snowy landscape, and icey regions\r<br />in Skyrim. You don&#39;t need to do anything extra to enjoy it.\r<br />\r<br />What you get:\r<br />- Snow that looks like real snow. And gives the impression of a much more accumulated snow on the ground. Snowy regions will be covered with more snow now.\r<br />- Icebergs, glaciers, and icefloes that look real. In reality, these do not look like icecubes in your soda&#33; Neither do they look like green glass&#33; Compare with real life photos and you&#39;ll see what I mean.\r<br />- Icicles that look like real icicles.\r<br />- Snowpaths that are covered more with snow, and footprints on snowpaths appear only during certain times of the day, and certain weather conditions.\r<br />- Fixed up road seams on snowy roads\r<br />\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />\r<br />     3. Save Games\r<br />\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />\r<br />Has nothing to do with them.\r<br />\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />\r<br />     4. Other Info / Credits\r<br />\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />Credits go to:\r<br />hodilton - for making the first demo video.\r<br />beatbox567 - for making the second demo video.\r<br />SC Gamingx - for showcasing the mod in their Weekly Spotlight series.\r<br />\r<br />\r<br />joshawowo - A BIG thank you to Joshawowo, the creator of Real Glass Armor, who sent me a very good explanation of how to make the icicles transparent, together with a descriptive screenshot. A help very much appreciated, where without him, I wouldn&#39;t even know where to start with this&#33;\r<br />\r<br />Thanks a lot guys&#33;\r<br />\r<br />If you find a bug or have anything to say, comment on the mod, or PM me\r<br />on the Nexus site.\r<br />\r<br />To use these textures in your work, please ask for permission first,\r<br />to see if I grant it to you. Thank you.\r<br />\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />\r<br />     5. Change Log\r<br />\r<br />*****************************************************************\r<br />\r<br />V1.1\r<br />\r<br />- added whiter and brighter glacier LODs\r<br />- to match LOD textures as much as possible, please use the Dark Ice optional\r<br />- to have bluer glaciers, please use the Dark Ice optional\r<br />- fixed snowrocks texture seam issue, as much as possible\r<br />- fixed snowrocks normal/alpha map issues\r<br />- fixed reflection and overall texture of frozen ice\r<br />- added bump on icefloes\r<br />- added whiter LOD snow textures\r<br />\r<br />V1.2 patch - this is an update, you need to download the main RIS file (v1.1), and overwrite it with this patch to get this working.\r<br />Use it if you want:\r<br />- brighter and whiter snow\r<br />- footprints on snowpath\r<br />\r<br />v1.3\r<br />- darkened ice floes.\r<br />- dark glacier textures are now default. Bright Ice is now an optional download.\r<br />- 3 different versions of snow: Bright, Medium, and Dark. Install the one you like.\r<br />- touched up some textures that needed color fixing.\r<br />- footprints on snowpath are now always visible.\r<br />- crystallized icicle is now the default icicle texture. ",
